int-org-section.p:
The Just Transition Fund was proposed in 2020 as part of the environment-orientated European Green Deal Investment Plan (see 
Environment
). Under the new MFF, the Just Transition Fund was allocated some €7,500m. in 2021–27, in 2018 prices, and some €10,000m. under the EU’s Next Generation EU recovery instrument. The Fund supports economic diversification in regions of member states that are expected to be negatively impacted by the transition towards climate neutrality.
